      <data key="e_body">Let me know how you want me to proceed with this information.  Michelle-----Original Message----- From: Watkins, Sherron Sent: Mon 11/19/2001 4:07 PM To: Cash, Michelle Cc: Sanders, Richard B.; Williams, Robert Subject: FW: Broadband litigation workMichelle, I have talked to Steven Sheldon, Martin Sacchi, and soon to talk to Marc Hensel and Ed Smida as well as Michele Nezi Marvin re: broadband litigation support work.  Luckily for the effort, I think all of these people, with the exception of Steven have a longer term position at broadband or elsewhere at Enron.  If this group of people or some subset thereof remains at Enron then I think we can get good litigation services from them re: broadband claims.  Call me if you have any questions.  Sherron. -----Original Message----- From:   Watkins, Sherron  Sent:   Friday, November 16, 2001 4:56 PM To:     Cash, Michelle Subject:        RE: Broadband litigation work I m wanting to use Martin Saachi and Steven Sheldon, both directors from EBS.  The quant work would be people from Vince s shop that are probably not as effected by the  surplusing .  I ll confirm Monday.  Thanks, Sherron. -----Original Message----- From:   Cash, Michelle  Sent:   Friday, November 16, 2001 4:39 PM To:     Watkins, Sherron Cc:     Sanders, Richard B. Subject:        RE: Broadband litigation work I need to have the names as soon as possible, even if they may choose not to do it.  Thanks.  Michelle  -----Original Message----- From:   Watkins, Sherron  Sent:   Friday, November 16, 2001 4:32 PM To:     Cash, Michelle Subject:        Broadband litigation work Michele - I have not yet gotten a hold of the 2 individuals I d like to work with on this.  Mark H. had asked me not speak to them until after I d met with Richard Sanders.  At any rate, I should be able to speak to them next week and get their names to you - I want to ensure that they want to work on the project.  I ll be in touch as soon as possible next week.  Regards, SherronSherron S. Watkins Vice President, Enron Corp. 713-345-8799 office 713-416-0620 cell</data>
