      <data key="e_body">Is Brooklyn Navy Yard deal still alive? Do you want us spending any time on this? -----Original Message-----From: 	Gottfredson, Bryan  Sent:	Monday, October 15, 2001 1:07 PMTo:	Shapiro, Richard; Steffes, James D.Cc:	Ibrahim, Amr; Yoho, Lisa; Montovano, SteveSubject:	New Deals for the week of Oct. 12Rick, Jim,	The following are the two deals that were presented at the RAC meeting last week, and should be communicated to Government Affairs:1.Region:  EWS/EA/East PowerDeal Name: Brooklyn Navy YardOriginator: David MarksDescription: Acquisition of 50% interest in 286 MW CCGT in Brooklyn, NY from Edison Mission Energy.  Edison has outstanding litigation with EPC Contractor and has 	      agreed to indemnify partnership and Enron for costs associated with outcome.GA Action Item: Inform Steve Montovano about new deal.2.Region: EWS/EELDeal Name: BOCOriginator: David GuyDescription: Sale of ETOL s oxygen business to BOC for approx $30 million; 15 year power supply agreement requiring $5m capex by ETOL.GA Action Item: Inform Lisa YohoThanks,Bryan713-345-2430</data>
